Gyasi Bawuah:¶

                                                            Topic:Is Black Panther Overhyped?

Black Panther, a 2018 fantasy/science fiction film, has received lots of attention since its release in the early parts of 2018. IMDb rates this movie 7.7 out of 10 , Rotten Tomatoes scores 96% , and Metacritic, 88% . Further, the website, Box Office Mojo, has stated that, Black Panther has earned $682,494,914 from domestic sales, as of April 24, 2018 . This is a great accomplishment for a movie of this kind. Several critics, professionals or non-professionals, have offered their views about Black Panther. Some believe this movie has achieved a historic feat, whiles others think the movie is having undue attention. Probably, either school of thought is accurate in their judgements. Would humans be more biased than machines, or machines more than humans? The purpose of this project is to compare the human ratings of the Black Panther movie to a machine learning model based on the sentiment analysis of the same movie.

In [8]:
black_panther = []

for sample in raw_data:
    user = sample.find('a').text
    date = sample.find("span", {"class":"review-date"}).text
    title = sample.find("div", {"class":"title"}).text
    content= sample.find("div", {"class":"content"}).text
    score = sample.find('span').text[-5:][0]
    
    black_panther.append((date, user, title, content, score))

# here we are going for strictly the sum:  add up the positives and "subtract" the negatives
# you can return a number or a label

def afinn_sent(inputstring):
    
    sentcount =0
    for word in inputstring.split():  
        if word.rstrip('?:!.,;') in afinn:
            sentcount = sentcount + afinn[word.rstrip('?:!.,;')]
            
    
    if (sentcount < 0):
        sentiment = 'Negative'
    elif (sentcount >0):
        sentiment = 'Positive'
    else:
        sentiment = 'Neutral'
    
    return sentiment
    #return sentcount
